SECTION 3: COMPLETE ICU WORKFLOW (For Every Patient)
====================================================================

WORKFLOW A: NEW PATIENT ADMISSION
===================================
TIME 0 (Patient Arrives):
  1. Duty Doctor opens app → Login with PIN
  2. Go to "🩺 ICU Frontline" tab
  3. Select "New Admission"
  4. Enter patient name, age, gender
  5. Assign ICU bed (from available beds list)
  6. Enter primary diagnosis category
  7. Fill vitals in the structured vitals section

TIME 0-15 MINUTES (Initial Assessment):
  8. Dictate full clinical history in the text area
     (or type notes → OR upload photo of paper notes)
  9. Upload ECG photo (taken with phone camera)
  10. Upload chest X-ray photo
  11. Upload any lab reports / ABG sheet

TIME 15-30 MINUTES (AI Analysis):
  12. Click "Quick Frontline Analysis" for routine case
      OR "Expert Board Review" for complex/critical case
      OR "Sepsis/Shock Protocol" if sepsis is suspected
  13. AI gives:
      - Working diagnosis
      - Criticality score (1-10 with RED/YELLOW/GREEN)
      - Treatment plan
      - Drug interactions
      - Investigation orders
  14. All data AUTO-SAVED to Google Sheets
  15. ICU Bed Board auto-updates

---

WORKFLOW B: DAILY HOD ROUND (Morning & Evening)
=================================================
HOD (Dr. Alok Sehgal or senior) logs in → goes to "📊 HOD Dashboard"
  1. See ALL active patients in one dashboard
  2. Each patient shows: Admitted date, total updates, last duty doctor
  3. Open any patient → See their complete Master Clinical File
  4. HOD can directly EDIT the master file in the text box
  5. Click "Save HOD Edits" → saved immediately
  6. To add NEW round findings:
     - Type in "Add Progress Note" box (same screen, no switching tabs!)
     - Upload new ABG / ECG / echo report
     - Click "Analyze Progress & Update Thread"
  7. AI automatically COMPARES new findings with yesterday's file
     - Tells you: "Patient is IMPROVING / DETERIORATING / STABLE"
     - Shows what changed and why
     - Creates updated master summary

---

WORKFLOW C: SHIFT HANDOVER (Every 8-12 Hours)
===============================================
OUTGOING DOCTOR:
  1. Go to "🔄 Shift Handover" tab
  2. Enter outgoing doctor name
  3. Enter incoming doctor name
  4. Add any pending tasks or concerns
  5. Click "Generate AI ISBAR Handover for ALL Active Patients"
  6. AI generates ISBAR format for EVERY active patient automatically
  7. Download as PDF → Sign → File

INCOMING DOCTOR:
  1. Login with their PIN
  2. Read the handover PDF or screen
  3. Go to ICU Bed Board → See bed-by-bed status
  4. Start their shift

---

WORKFLOW D: DETERIORATING PATIENT EMERGENCY
=============================================
1. Nurse alerts duty doctor: "Patient in Bed X deteriorating"
2. Doctor opens "🚨 Early Warning" tab
3. Enter current vitals → Calculate NEWS2 Score instantly
   - Score ≥ 7 (RED): IMMEDIATE action, call HOD
   - Score 5-6 (ORANGE): Urgent review in 30 min
   - Score 3-4 (YELLOW): Review in 1 hour
4. If sepsis suspected: Run qSOFA calculator
5. Click "AI Deterioration Analysis" → paste trends → AI predicts complications
6. Go to "ICU Frontline" → Add Emergency Progress Note → "Expert Board Review"
7. AI gives emergency management protocol

---

WORKFLOW E: DISCHARGE PLANNING
================================
1. HOD Dashboard → Open patient file
2. Scroll to bottom → Click "Generate Discharge Summary"
3. AI reads ENTIRE clinical journey (all notes, all updates) and auto-generates:
   - Admission diagnosis
   - Summary of ICU stay
   - Discharge medications with doses
   - Follow-up instructions
   - Red flag symptoms
4. Download Discharge Summary PDF
5. Click "Mark as Discharged" → Bed becomes available automatically

